emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group of boys, girls, men, and women, including nurse, standing on wooden dock, including group of boys on left and group of girls on right seated on dock, at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured."
